div.p:
The Third being for Gentlemen to learn the necessary Arts and Exercises, to qualify them for the Service of their Countrey, and entertaining them one whole year at the Publick Charge, may be suppos'd to have always One thousand Persons on its hands, and cannot have less than 100 Teachers; who I wou'd thus order;
Every Teacher shall continue at least One year, but by allowance Two years at most; shall have 20 l. per Ann. Extraordinary Allowance; shall be bound to give their constant Attendance, and shall have always 5 College-Majors of the Second College to supervise them, who shall command a Month, and then be succeeded by 5


others, and so on; 10 l. per Ann. extraordinary to be paid them for their Attendance.
